Grateful to spend time in White Mesa with the Ute Mountain Ute Tribe alongside @RepBurgessOwens and @RepJeffHurd to discuss education, community, and environmental priorities.

We also toured the White Mesa Mill in San Juan County. The mill is the only uranium processing facility in the U.S. and a vital piece of our national security. I first visited in April, and I was proud to bring colleagues back to see the incredible work happening here in Utah. Thank you to the community leaders and everyone who welcomed us.

Last week, an EF-2 tornado struck in San Juan County, destroying homes and leaving lasting damage. We are grateful no lives were lost, but for the families directly impacted, the work of recovery has only just begun.

In the days since, I’ve been in touch with local leaders to ensure resources are available and our agencies are responsive to community needs. Utahns know how to rally together in times of hardship, and I have no doubt we will help our neighbors rebuild stronger than before.

If you or someone you know was affected and needs assistance, please don’t hesitate to reach out to my office.

I’m honored to have co-led the resolution honoring Charlie Kirk’s lifelong commitment to free speech and civil debate. 

Today, the House reaffirmed that violence will not silence truth and Charlie’s legacy will endure. https://t.co/7RkcbBazRt

On this day 238 years ago our Founders signed the U.S. Constitution — the greatest foundational document in history.

Today, we renew our commitment to defending the God-given freedoms they secured for us.

Honored to spend some time with Utah County community for their National Day of Service. 

I’m proud to represent a community of people so committed to making a difference. https://t.co/39oWzUxgvI

I visited Timpanogos Regional Hospital, where Charlie was brought. It was truly touching to see the tributes, a clear reminder to me of how many people he inspired and how much love there is here in Utah. https://t.co/cr6rWi7Sk5

I would like to express my gratitude to the FBI, Kash Patel, the US Marshalls, Sheriff Smith, Utah law enforcement, and Governor Spencer Cox for their work in bringing the suspected assassin into custody. I am incredibly thankful to all those who worked on this case, including the many citizens who provided information for law enforcement officers. 

I send my sympathies to all those affected—especially to Charlie Kirk’s two children and wife, Erika. I stand with you, and I am confident that the full force of the American legal system will deliver justice for Charlie and for your family.
 
We will not allow an act of evil to silence the American people. Charlie’s legacy of free speech and commitment to civil discussion will live on. Violence will not intimidate us and violence will not silence us.

Read the resolution here:
https://t.co/hIqCUFSh0E

I have introduced a House Resolution condemning the cowardly attack that took Charlie Kirk’s life and honoring his commitment to the constitutional freedom of speech.

This deranged act was not only an attack on Charlie Kirk, leaving behind his incredible wife and two young children, but an attack on Americans and the values that our country is founded upon.

Our hearts are broken, but our resolve is firm: justice will be served, and we will honor Charlie’s legacy by continuing to speak boldly for faith, freedom, and our nation.

Today, on 9/11, we remember the thousands of lives lost to an act of terror meant to silence America. 

Today, we also mourn Charlie Kirk, whose life was taken in another act of violence against America.

These tragedies remind us that we cannot let violence curtail our God given rights. On this day, we honor those we’ve lost by renewing our commitment to our republic, defending free speech, and never letting violent acts of hate or terror keep us from standing for what we believe in.

Violence will not silence the American people.

We must make this a Turning Point for our country and carry on Charlie’s legacy. https://t.co/13UNgwOKJD

There is no place for political violence in our country.

Charlie Kirk is a husband, father, and American who admirably fought for what he believes in. 

I join Utahns and our great nation in praying for his family and all those impacted by this loss.

I’m devastated to learn Charlie Kirk was shot during an event at UVU. We condemn this senseless act of violence. Praying for Charlie and all those affected. My team and I are monitoring the situation for updates.

Read more about the POST Act here:

https://t.co/G2Kd5Qc5ms

I came to Washington with a goal to hold government accountable and fix broken systems. 

I’m proud to announce the House passed my Personnel Oversight and Shift Tracking Act, a commonsense reform that cuts waste and inefficiency. https://t.co/4SDEGb9nnF

This week in Washington, the House passed the FY26 Energy & Water Appropriations bill, a positive step toward regular-order budgeting.

I voted to restore American energy dominance, drive down costs, and deliver critical funding for Utah, including:
✅ Uintah County water infrastructure
✅ Central Utah Project
✅ Uranium remediation in Grand County

And we eliminated:
❌ Wasteful Biden-era offices 
❌ Woke DEI programs

H.R. 1, “The Working Family Tax Cuts”, is delivering for Utah and America's national security:

- A 20% tax cut for 69,000 Utah small businesses
- 72,000 Utah jobs protected
- Major investment in Utahs aerospace and defense manufacturing
- A stronger U.S. drone industrial base, so America, not China, sets the standard.

Watch my remarks on how the bill strengthens Utah’s industries, supports our workers, and keeps America competitive at home and ahead of China abroad.

Thank you to Chief Hales and the Wasatch County Fire District for briefing my team on their outstanding work. My Utah Wildfire Research Institute Act will put our state on equal footing with other states by establishing Utah’s first federal wildfire institute. I am committed to ensuring Utah has the same federal resources to tackle wildfires as other states while also supporting the firefighters and first responders who work tirelessly to protect Utah’s forests and communities.

Last week, I toured the Chevron Refinery to discuss their operations and their role in advancing American Energy Dominance. The refinery produces gasoline, diesel, and jet fuel, with 30% of its oil sourced locally in Utah. I remain committed to supporting America’s growing energy demands.

I had the honor of meeting Annabelle Leek, a student from Copper Hills High School, at Camp Williams today. She delivered an inspiring, award-winning essay that she wrote. As a dedicated student-athlete, Annabelle truly embodies the spirit of what it means to be an American patriot.
Utah is leading the way in drone innovation and implementation for the American warfighter. Prioritizing drone technology will strengthen and secure the future of our military.

I appreciated discussing immigration at today’s panel. Utahns deserve real answers, not political games. We need both secure borders and legal pathways that work. I will keep fighting to uphold the rule of law, improve our immigration system, and put America first.

Katrina and I, along with my team, are devastated by the tragic news from Tremonton. Our hearts go out to the families of the officers who lost their lives and to the deputy injured in this senseless act of violence. We pray for their loved ones and for the swift recovery of the injured deputy. Violence has no place in our communities, and we stand in solidarity with those affected by this tragedy.

I’m grateful for the swift response of our courageous firefighters battling the blaze south of Slate Canyon. My team and I are closely monitoring the situation and praying for a safe and swift resolution. https://t.co/KDGHd1ouM6

I had a great time speaking with the wonderful people at BioUtah. The life sciences are crucial to Utah’s thriving economy. Thank you to BioUtah and BYU for their warm hospitality. https://t.co/e6Q4GyZCJF

I enjoyed joining my friend and colleague, @RepBurgessOwens, at the Provo City Library for an in-person town hall this morning. Thank you to the Utah County Liberty Forum for hosting this public event and to law enforcement for ensuring a respectful and civil dialogue. https://t.co/TZjXJgWjx7

I commend the administration’s decision to expedite the environmental review process for the Skyline coal mine. This will empower Utah’s 3rd district to help America achieve energy dominance by harnessing all energy sources, including coal, oil, natural gas, nuclear, wind, solar, and hydropower. https://t.co/BRklmClDt4

Good News for Utah! President Trump’s Oval Office announcement of Apple’s manufacturing expansion in Lehi, part of their $600 billion investment in America, will create high-paying jobs, strengthen our local economy, and ensure that critical technology, like semiconductors, is produced right here in Utah’s 3rd District.

https://t.co/ovSRr4hGhP
My team and I held productive meetings with the Daggett County Commission. Addressing the needs of my constituents, regardless of the county's size, remains my top priority. https://t.co/jvku6DpR98

Yesterday, Katrina and I had the honor of meeting the Stice sisters, who shared their remarkable story of growing up in the historic pioneer-era log home now located in Heritage Park, Highland, Utah. Their history of resilience and courage embodies true American triumph. The home, built around 1890, was occupied by the Stice family from 1926 to 1954. Today, it stands as a cherished reminder of the past for visitors from across the state, country, and world to enjoy. A heartfelt thank you to the Stice sisters for sharing their inspiring story with us and the entire community.

Open dialogue is at the heart of our republic, and is part of what makes this nation great. 

I’ll be in Vernal and Roosevelt on Thursday, July 31st to uphold that spirit and hear directly from you.

As mentioned in my recent telephone town hall, I will be holding an in-person town hall in Dutch John, Utah, on Tuesday, July 29th at 4 PM. Due to limited space, only those with RSVP-confirmed tickets will be admitted. RSVP here: https://t.co/HOR0K6oi4C https://t.co/ScjzVLSWTr

Thank you to all 15,000+ who tuned in to my telephone town hall tonight. We covered the Epstein files, Medicaid reform, support for our veterans, and more. Utahns want common sense, accountability, and transparency. I’m taking that message back to Washington. https://t.co/fImJluWjmc

On this Pioneer Day, we honor the remarkable journey of the pioneers, whose courage, steadfast faith in God, and unyielding determination triumphed over immense challenges and inspired our forefathers. Join me in celebrating their enduring spirit! Happy Pioneer Day, Utah! https://t.co/J0dqc6UZ47

Big step forward: My bill, the Utah Wildfire Research Institute Act, passed the @NatResources Committee!

This bill gives Utah access to critical wildfire resources so we can better research, mitigate, and respond to wildfires. https://t.co/0nalm3OB1D

Grateful to Brian Steed, Executive Director of Utah State University’s Institute for Land, Water, and Air, for joining the @WesternCaucus to discuss Western water issues and my bill, the Utah Wildfire Research Institute Act of 2025. Utah continues to lead the way on land, water, and wildfire policy.

Recent news from Price, highlights the extraordinary work of our law enforcement. The Carbon Metro Drug Task Force conducted a raid, seizing several pounds of drugs and multiple weapons from a home located next to a daycare. This action is a stark reminder of the dangers in our communities and the heroes who stand against them. I’m moved by the efforts of our law enforcement who strive to protect our communities, day in and day out.

Major victory for financial freedom! This week, the House passed H.R. 1919, the Anti-CBDC Surveillance State Act which I co-sponsored, and H.R. 3633, the Digital Asset Market Clarity Act. These laws will bring clarity to digital assets and protect Americans from government surveillance through CBDCs.

When I was a state senator in Utah, I led the charge to exclude CBDC from our state’s definition of money alongside @Clancy4Utah. Now, as your Congressman, I’m honored to continue this fight on the national level.

Early this morning, I voted in favor of the House’s Rescissions Act, cutting $9 billion in wasteful spending, fraud, and abuse. Along with my colleagues in the @HouseGOP, I’m committed to tackling our national debt crisis with common-sense solutions, ensuring our tax dollars are used wisely to strengthen our communities and secure a bright future for the United States of America and Utah.
For real-time updates on the Deer Creek Fire in San Juan County, visit https://t.co/vlMudKDrIc or follow @UtahWildfire on social media. https://t.co/lH96OfYQwv
My team and I continue to closely monitor the Deer Creek fire in San Juan County. Our brave firefighters are working tirelessly to protect our communities and landscapes. https://t.co/MDFftSk18F

My team and I are actively monitoring the Deer Creek fire near La Sal in San Juan County. I extend my heartfelt support to the brave firefighters battling this blaze and pray for their safety and the well-being of La Sal’s residents. I am committed to ensuring they receive all necessary support. Protecting the lives and livelihoods of our hardworking families remains my top priority.

On this Independence Day, whether you're watching a parade, marveling at a fireworks display, or gathering with loved ones, Katrina and I join you in celebrating the land of the free and the home of the brave. Let us honor the sacrifices of those who fought for our liberty and stand together to cherish and protect our freedoms. Happy Fourth of July! 🇺🇸
Today I voted YES on H.R. 1, the One Big Beautiful Bill Act. https://t.co/6tSQPQNfO1

Yesterday I took the House floor to make one thing clear:
Medicaid must be preserved for those who truly need it by protecting the vulnerable and rooting out fraud, waste, and abuse.

I’m grateful that key provisions from my Ensuring Medicaid Eligibility Act of 2025 were secured in this landmark legislation—helping ensure support reaches those who qualify and rely on it.

The One Big Beautiful Bill proves we don’t have to choose. We can protect those in need and stop the waste.

Katrina and I are heartbroken over the horrific ambush in Coeur d’Alene, Idaho, where brave first responders were targeted while serving their community. My heart aches for those affected, and I’m committed to standing with American communities in times of tragedy. Our first responders risk their lives daily to keep us safe, and this senseless violence against them is unacceptable.
This is a massive pro-life victory. The Supreme Court just cleared the way for states to stop sending Medicaid funds to Planned Parenthood. Taxpayers should never be forced to fund abortion.

@SenMikeLee is right—Washington has locked up our land and made it too hard for states and communities to meet local housing needs. I’m committed to ensuring we empower local leaders to grow responsibly while prioritizing our farmers, ranchers, and recreational users. That work continues, even as Congress determines the best path forward.

The Supreme Court’s unanimous decision to uphold the approval of the Uinta Basin Railway represents a significant advancement for America’s energy infrastructure and a vital boost to rural economic development in Utah. Prior to this ruling, NEPA was used by agencies and interest groups to delay or block projects, hindering growth in rural communities. By affirming the project’s approval, the Court has empowered local and state governments to pursue development opportunities that directly benefit Utah residents.

Fixing critical programs like Medicaid and SNAP is one of the reasons I ran for Congress. I’m proud that President Trump’s Big Beautiful Bill includes key reforms from my Ensuring Medicaid Eligibility Act and Let’s Get to Work Act to make sure support reaches those who truly need it.

I voted to advance President Trump’s One Big Beautiful bill—a commonsense package that delivers real results by: 

 ✅ Prioritizing American families and businesses 

✅Strengthening SNAP work requirements 

✅Eliminating waste, fraud, and abuse in Medicaid

✅ Bolstering U.S. border security and our economy 

✅ Unleashing American energy dominance
